- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the development of a computer-aided clinical decision support system for breast cancer screening, which has implications for healthcare and society.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper describes the use of machine learning algorithms to learn personalized screening policies from electronic health record data.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on the development of a machine learning algorithm to learn personalized screening policies.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the use of a computer-aided clinical decision support system to assist healthcare providers in making screening decisions.
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper utilizes electronic health record data to learn personalized screening policies.
